cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image data and the extraction of tree-skeletons from volumetric brain image data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with the analysis of neurons and their shapes. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of methods derived from persistent homology. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the paper deals with the development of new approaches for neuroscientific data analysis. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possibility as the paper deals with the visualization and summarization of neuronal shapes.
